00-3909, Nov. 2012.[41]J. B. Seo, and V. C. M. Leung, ” Design and analysis of backoff algorithms for random access channels in UMTS-LTE and IEEE 802.16 systems,” IEEE Trans. on Vehicular Technology, vol. 60, no. 8, pp. 3975 - 3989, Oct. 2011.[42]S. Kim, J. Cha, S. Jung, S. Jung, C. Yoon, and K. Lim, “Performance evaluation of random access for M2M communication on IEEE 802.16 network,” 14th International Conference Advanced Communication Technology, Feb. 2012.[43]W. Yue, "The effect of capture on Performance of Multichannel Slotted ALOHA Systems," IEEE Trans. Communications, vol. 39. pp. 818-822, June1991.[44]H. Inaltekin, and S. B. Wicker, “The analysis of Nash Equilibria of the one-shot random-access game for wireless networks and the behavior of selfish nodes,” IEEE/ACM Trans. on Networking, vol. 16, no. 5, pp. 1094-1107, Oct. 2008.[45]H. Inaltekin, and S. B. Wicher, “A one-shot random access game for wireless networks,” in Proc. 2005 International Conference on Wireless Networks, Communications and Mobile Computing, pp. 940-945, Jun. 2005.[46]L. G. Roberts, and D. C. Washington, “ALOHA packet system with and without slots and capture,” ACM SIGCOMM Computer Communication Review, vol. 5, no. 2, pp. 28-42, Apr. 1975.[47]A. B. Behroozi-Toosi,  and R. R. Rao, “Delay upper bounds for a finite user random-access system with bursty arrivals,” IEEE Trans. on Communications, vol. 40, no. 3, pp.591-596, Mar. 1992.[48]I. Robin, “Synchronous and channel-sense asynchronous dynamic group-random-access schemes for multiple-access communications,” IEEE Trans. on Communications, vol. 31, pp. 1063-1077, Sep. 1983.[49]Q. Ren and H. Kobayashi, “Transient analysis of media access protocols by diffusion approximation,” Digest of the 1995 International Symposium of Information Theory, Whistler, Canada, Sep. 1995.[50]3GPP TS 36.211, “Evolved universal terrestrial radio access (E-UTRA): Physical channels and modulation,” V10.2.0, June 2011.
